contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

04:27.690 --> 04:29.678
Hey, Andy,
you got a warrant for Drew?

04:29.694 --> 04:31.678
Turns out he really hated
his old man.

04:31.690 --> 04:32.771
That's not exactly a crime.

04:33.642 --> 04:35.282
Except if your old man's
been knocked off.

04:35.642 --> 04:38.202
We've already interviewed him. It
was the first place we started.

04:38.454 --> 04:39.694
He was pretty intense in court.

04:39.710 --> 04:43.698
Intense? The man has just lost
both his parents.

04:43.714 --> 04:45.734
Then he has to stand up
in front of the whole world

04:46.650 --> 04:48.638
and explain how his father
raped his sister?

04:48.650 --> 04:49.714
I'd be fuckin' intense too.

04:49.730 --> 04:52.670
I know, but if he's got motive,
we need to eliminate him.

04:52.686 --> 04:54.710
He's already been eliminated.
Not forensically.

04:54.722 --> 04:56.662
We've never looked at him

04:56.678 --> 04:57.714
for any physical connection
to the crime.

04:57.730 --> 05:02.662
Right.
No, that's true, that's true.

05:05.726 --> 05:07.714
If that little prick
has set me up...

05:09.662 --> 05:11.718
..that would mean that whole
phone call thing

05:11.730 --> 05:14.726
could've been bullshit.

05:14.982 --> 05:16.702
I don't understand.
I haven't done anything.

05:16.718 --> 05:18.710
I called you that night
to see if you were home.

05:18.726 --> 05:21.718
And I was. You came over to see me
for an hour or more.

05:21.734 --> 05:24.638
We talked about Dad, mostly.
You remember that.

05:24.654 --> 05:26.658
I called you on your mobile.
You could've been anywhere.

05:26.674 --> 05:29.646
I was at home.
I came home after court.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.678
Or you went straight to Steve's
to knock him off.

05:31.694 --> 05:33.658
Then you raced back here
to meet me.

05:33.674 --> 05:35.698
To let me provide you
with the world's best alibi.

05:35.714 --> 05:38.698
Because who's gonna question me,
right? That's what you thought.

05:38.714 --> 05:40.686
No. No!
Then Dianne Vasilich turns up.

05:40.702 --> 05:43.658
Very bloody handy! I do not like
to be made to look like a liar!

05:43.674 --> 05:45.682
Drew, if there's anything
you want to tell us,

05:45.694 --> 05:47.690
courts like an early guilty plea.

05:47.702 --> 05:48.706
What?

05:48.722 --> 05:50.718
Then you took the chance
to pay Steve back

05:50.730 --> 05:52.694
for a childhood disagreement.

05:52.706 --> 05:54.714
He was my friend!

05:54.730 --> 05:57.650
You little prick!
He was a decent bloke!

05:57.662 --> 05:58.698
He killed my mother.

06:02.670 --> 06:05.710
Seeing her like that
made him feel weak,

06:05.722 --> 06:08.722
and he couldn't handle it.

06:10.654 --> 06:12.662
What'd you do to him?

06:12.678 --> 06:14.690
I told him I was glad
he was going to jail.

06:14.702 --> 06:16.682
The arsehole. We had a fight.

06:16.698 --> 06:19.726
He was so furious,
he just kept yelling.

06:20.642 --> 06:22.443
I thought he was going to have
a heart attack.

06:24.686 --> 06:29.730
And then he pushed me.
He shoved me into the wall.

06:30.646 --> 06:32.686
I thought he was going to kill me,
he was so strong.

06:36.682 --> 06:38.670
I just wanted him to stop.

06:49.638 --> 06:51.678
Forensics found soil and
some tiny seeds in his car,

06:51.694 --> 06:53.646
under the accelerator pedal.

06:53.662 --> 06:54.718
They must have dropped
off his shoes.

06:54.734 --> 06:56.814
The dirt and the seeds are
particular from one area -

06:57.642 --> 06:58.690
Gerringong.

06:58.706 --> 07:00.714
Drew buried
Steven Blakely's body.

07:00.730 --> 07:02.722
Oh, he killed him too,
don't worry about that.

07:03.238 --> 07:04.678
His DNA was all over
the cricket bat.

07:04.694 --> 07:07.646
We assumed it was his, or he
and his father played with it,

07:07.658 --> 07:08.694
but the bat belonged to Maya.

07:08.706 --> 07:10.642
Oh, a crime of passion.

07:10.658 --> 07:12.658
He's not going to succeed
with self-defence.

07:12.674 --> 07:16.638
After he hit Blakely, Dianne
arrived through the back door.

07:16.654 --> 07:18.710
Yep. He hid in the study,
heard someone come in, yelling.

07:18.726 --> 07:21.658
Then silence,
then the same steps racing out.

07:21.674 --> 07:23.722
So, Occam's Razor
is a load of hogwash.

07:24.638 --> 07:27.646
So if anyone's to say 'I told
you so', now's your chance.

07:27.658 --> 07:28.694
The bomb attack?

07:28.710 --> 07:30.710
He says he doesn't know
anything about it.

07:30.726 --> 07:32.702
We've still got the team
looking at that.

07:32.718 --> 07:35.674
If there is anything to find,
Janet, we will find it.

07:35.690 --> 07:38.646
We've turned his house
and his car inside out.

07:38.662 --> 07:40.690
I'll keep looking, but,
you know,

07:40.706 --> 07:43.706
this could just be a messed-up kid
who hated his father.

07:43.722 --> 07:45.706
The murder of Steven Blakely
was an isolated incident.

07:45.718 --> 07:46.734
Are you serious?

07:47.329 --> 07:48.690
As much as I hate to say it,
Janet,

07:48.706 --> 07:51.694
Steven Blakely was the one who was
connected to Moreno and Nelson,

07:51.706 --> 07:53.638
and maybe Renmark too.

07:53.654 --> 07:55.650
It might be the reason
he killed Sally.

08:06.726 --> 08:10.638
Ah, Jack, sorry,
have you got a minute?

08:11.642 --> 08:12.686
See ya.

08:22.646 --> 08:26.674
Is charging Drew the right thing
to be doing at this stage?

08:26.686 --> 08:28.670
Absolutely it is, yeah.

08:28.686 --> 08:29.722
What if he does have
some connection

08:29.734 --> 08:31.674
to Moreno and the rest of them?

08:31.690 --> 08:33.674
There's nothing linking
the two of them...

08:33.686 --> 08:35.662
Because they've retaliated before.

08:36.706 --> 08:40.654
We'll keep security detail on you
as long as we need to.

08:40.669 --> 08:42.638
Don't you worry about that.
Great.

08:42.654 --> 08:45.670
So my family and I keep
living apart indefinitely?

08:45.686 --> 08:48.670
We will find out.
You can't promise me that.

08:49.670 --> 08:50.718
No, I can't.

08:52.682 --> 08:54.718
I want my life back.

09:03.682 --> 09:06.646
It's just a matter of time,
Janet.

09:07.678 --> 09:10.694
These people are rattled.
They'll make mistakes.

09:10.710 --> 09:12.694
Yeah, it's the mistakes
I'm worried about.

09:12.710 --> 09:16.710
I will sort this. That's not
a promise, but I do believe it.

09:33.702 --> 09:35.702
Thanks for coming in,
Mrs Moreno.

09:37.726 --> 09:39.706
I don't understand.

09:39.722 --> 09:42.714
There were cameras hidden
in the house.

09:43.714 --> 09:45.650
Who?

09:45.666 --> 09:48.654
The police are finalising their
investigations at the moment.

09:50.650 --> 09:52.090
We went to that house
more than once.

09:52.638 --> 09:53.734
Is that the only photo,

09:54.650 --> 09:56.690
or just the only one
you've found so far?

09:56.706 --> 09:59.638
Are there hundreds of photos
of Ruby floating around?

09:59.654 --> 10:01.670
This is the only photo we need
to prosecute.

10:09.710 --> 10:13.650
This is a still from a video.
Yes.

10:13.666 --> 10:16.694
She's taking off a bikini top.
The video didn't stop here.

10:16.710 --> 10:20.658
She'd take off her whole top,
and maybe the bottom half too.

10:20.670 --> 10:21.706
She would be naked.

10:21.722 --> 10:24.706
We don't know
where the video ends.

10:24.722 --> 10:26.702
But they wouldn't stop
at this still.

10:26.714 --> 10:28.642
They would use the rest of it.

10:28.658 --> 10:30.178
They would sell
the rest of the stills.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.706
After everything with Alex,

10:33.722 --> 10:36.666
attacking an artist's integrity,
and now this?

10:36.678 --> 10:39.658
These people have to be stopped,

10:39.674 --> 10:41.706
but we need your help
to convict Timothy Clarke,

10:41.722 --> 10:44.698
the man we found with this photo
on his computer.

10:44.714 --> 10:48.662
A photo he bought from Russia?
A Russian website.

10:51.646 --> 10:54.678
Don't they understand
that these are real children?

11:00.726 --> 11:03.642
What do you need?

11:03.658 --> 11:05.642
We need to prove
your daughter's age.

11:05.654 --> 11:06.670
Birth certificate?

11:06.686 --> 11:10.646
The defence won't accept that, I'm
afraid. We'll need you in court.

11:10.662 --> 11:13.678
Me?
Yes.

11:14.678 --> 11:15.734
And her photo?

11:16.646 --> 11:17.730
We'll need to use that too.

11:18.646 --> 11:20.734
Without it, and your testimony,
we have no case.

11:21.182 --> 11:22.702
The best thing you can do
at this point

11:22.718 --> 11:24.718
is help to convict the man
who has this photo.

11:24.734 --> 11:26.730
You'll be helping to protect
other children.

11:27.413 --> 11:29.694
By letting more and more people
see my daughter like this?

11:29.710 --> 11:32.686
Letting them imagine
what comes next?

11:32.698 --> 11:33.734
I'm sorry.

11:35.686 --> 11:37.674
I'll have to think about it.

11:47.694 --> 11:50.718
There's not too many decent blokes
left these days.

11:50.730 --> 11:53.666
All bloody corporate types.

11:53.682 --> 11:56.718
They come into the force, you know,
with MBAs shoved up their arses.

11:56.734 --> 12:01.650
They all want careers, vocational
training, KPI assessments.

12:01.666 --> 12:04.658
Whatever happened to bloody getting
scumbags off the street, huh?

12:04.674 --> 12:06.682
Andy Campbell?

12:08.674 --> 12:11.730
You're joking. Shit.
Better bring him in.

12:12.730 --> 12:14.682
Something actually go right?

12:14.698 --> 12:18.650
DNA results on items from
the Oriana Vasilich murder scene.

12:18.666 --> 12:20.702
Positive match.
Finally got the bastard.

12:23.650 --> 12:25.730
Danny Novak, put your hands
where I can see them.

12:26.642 --> 12:27.722
Oh, what the fuck!

12:28.638 --> 12:30.678
Put your hands up! Up!
Get up! Now!

12:30.694 --> 12:32.658
I haven't finished my coffee yet.
Do you mind?

12:32.674 --> 12:33.706
What are you doing?
Move!

12:33.718 --> 12:36.694
Let him go! Dad! Dad!

12:36.710 --> 12:40.674
You can't do this. He has rights.
He's got rights!

12:40.690 --> 12:43.686
Mind my head.
Dad!

13:01.662 --> 13:03.714
Tatum?
I can give you five minutes.

13:03.730 --> 13:06.702
Are you sure that's OK?
Yeah, just five minutes, OK?

13:21.706 --> 13:26.686
Sorry it took so long. Did you
get a cup of tea out of 'em?

13:28.658 --> 13:31.670
They only just put these back on.
They obviously don't trust you.

13:32.686 --> 13:35.638
Do you need anything?
Water, or...?

13:35.650 --> 13:36.710
No, no, no, I'm fine.

13:36.726 --> 13:38.726
Nobody will tell me anything
about what's going on.

13:38.730 --> 13:41.694
It's a mistake, sweetheart.
They're harassing you.

13:41.710 --> 13:43.702
No, it's just like
searching the house.

13:43.718 --> 13:46.678
They're getting their stats up
for the month, that's all.

13:49.706 --> 13:54.686
It's that girl, isn't it?
Oriana Vasilich?

13:55.730 --> 13:58.646
There's nothing in it.

13:59.722 --> 14:03.658
Well, you didn't know who she was.
Exactly.

14:03.674 --> 14:05.194
That's what I keep trying
to tell them.

14:05.646 --> 14:07.670
It was so long ago.
I mean, nearly two decades.

14:07.686 --> 14:10.682
People are bound to get things
wrong, make mistakes.

14:10.698 --> 14:14.690
Exactly. So go back to work,
sweetheart. I'll see you at home.

14:15.690 --> 14:19.690
OK. It's my turn to cook.
Yeah, can't wait.

14:24.694 --> 14:26.686
See ya.

14:39.702 --> 14:41.690
Hey.

14:41.706 --> 14:45.650
You OK?
You came.

14:45.666 --> 14:48.682
Of course I did.
They think he killed that girl.

14:48.698 --> 14:52.642
I know. Andy called Janet.
Everybody knows?

14:56.658 --> 14:59.642
They probably know more than I do,
which wouldn't be hard.

15:01.658 --> 15:03.690
How was she killed?
I don't know, exactly.

15:03.706 --> 15:06.658
Bullshit.
I'm gonna hear eventually.

15:06.674 --> 15:09.658
Her body was never found
so nobody really knows.

15:10.722 --> 15:14.642
No body. That makes prosecution
pretty difficult.

15:14.654 --> 15:15.694
Yeah, it can.

15:15.710 --> 15:17.702
And Oriana, she was blackmailing

15:17.718 --> 15:19.710
politicians
and all sorts of people.

15:19.726 --> 15:23.718
God knows what else she was up to.
Not exactly a model citizen.

15:24.718 --> 15:27.718
I'm so sorry.
There's nothing to be sorry for.

15:27.734 --> 15:30.654
I know how you feel
about your dad.

15:33.662 --> 15:37.654
My Dad never hit me
when I was growing up. Never.

15:37.666 --> 15:38.726
He never raised his voice.

15:39.642 --> 15:40.882
He read me stories every night,

15:41.646 --> 15:43.007
sitting on the floor
beside my bed.

15:43.646 --> 15:47.678
And if I got scared by a giant
or werewolf or witch,

15:47.694 --> 15:50.710
he would stay there on the floor
until I fell asleep.

15:51.710 --> 15:54.722
One morning he was still there
when I woke up, fast asleep.

15:54.734 --> 15:57.726
He never missed a sports match

15:58.642 --> 16:01.654
or a music performance
or a speech night.

16:03.718 --> 16:07.690
He cooked sausages at fundraisers
and sold charity chocolates

16:07.706 --> 16:10.690
to his workmates and
he taught me to play tennis.

16:10.702 --> 16:12.638
Come here.

16:24.694 --> 16:26.722
The Nelson jury are
on their way back.

16:26.734 --> 16:28.666
It's too quick.

16:28.682 --> 16:30.650
Doesn't necessarily mean
an acquittal.

16:30.662 --> 16:31.666
Drew's derailed it.

16:31.682 --> 16:32.730
Once he's convicted,
we've got grounds for appeal,

16:33.642 --> 16:34.682
