31:04.686 --> 31:07.646
Oh, could fuck us up for years.

31:07.662 --> 31:09.718
Hundreds of decisions
overturned.

31:09.730 --> 31:12.642
The State'll be in a mess,

31:12.658 --> 31:15.686
and God knows how many crims
just roaming around.

31:19.726 --> 31:21.730
You've been amazing
through all this.

31:22.646 --> 31:28.650
I don't know how you carried on.
I know I couldn't have.

31:30.718 --> 31:32.702
You're a fine human being.

31:35.642 --> 31:37.682
You really are.

31:39.642 --> 31:41.678
Don't you dare make me cry.

31:43.694 --> 31:46.678
Make us both cry,
we'll really be in trouble.

31:48.674 --> 31:52.686
Alright, that's it.
Back to the fray.

31:52.698 --> 31:54.646
All this wasn't the fray?

31:54.662 --> 31:57.706
Oh, Tracey has about 300 files
with your name on them.

31:57.718 --> 31:58.722
Thank you.

31:59.638 --> 32:02.158
And if you tell anyone I went soft
on you, I'll deny everything.

32:08.678 --> 32:10.726
Good news, thank the Lord.

32:11.329 --> 32:12.690
If you want to back up that truck,

32:12.706 --> 32:15.642
I'm ready to tackle
any files you have waiting.

32:15.658 --> 32:19.678
I don't believe anyone's ever
accused me

32:19.690 --> 32:21.658
of being a truck driver before.

32:31.694 --> 32:33.718
Ms Badir,
you've heard the summary,

32:33.734 --> 32:36.710
and you wish to plead guilty
to common assault, is that correct?

32:36.722 --> 32:38.710
Yes. Yes, Your Honour.

32:38.726 --> 32:41.638
Are you ready to proceed
with the plea now?

32:41.650 --> 32:42.678
I am, Your Honour.

32:45.642 --> 32:46.702
As an officer of the law,

32:46.718 --> 32:50.658
I should know better than anyone
else what constitutes assault.

32:50.674 --> 32:55.654
Despite this, I attacked
the victim, Mr Clarke,

32:55.670 --> 32:59.706
without any reason
or provocation.

32:59.722 --> 33:02.666
To say that I'm humiliated by
my own actions

33:02.682 --> 33:04.678
would be a great understatement.

33:04.690 --> 33:06.706
I am appalled by what I did.

33:06.718 --> 33:09.718
I'm not excusing my behaviour,

33:09.730 --> 33:12.726
but all I can say in mitigation,

33:13.642 --> 33:15.706
Your Honour, is that I operated

33:15.722 --> 33:18.686
at the time
under a misapprehension

33:18.702 --> 33:22.714
that the young girl in question
needed my protection.

33:22.730 --> 33:26.638
If the young girl
was in no way distressed,

33:26.654 --> 33:28.646
why did you think
she needed your help?

33:28.658 --> 33:29.682
Well, I...

33:32.686 --> 33:35.686
It's just a feeling I had,
Your Honour.

33:35.698 --> 33:38.714
A feeling? I see.

33:40.682 --> 33:43.686
As a solicitor,
I deeply regret my actions,

33:43.702 --> 33:46.670
and I can assure you there's no
need for specific deterrence,

33:46.682 --> 33:48.650
as I will not be doing this again.

33:48.666 --> 33:52.662
Usually on a charge such as this,
I would take into consideration

33:52.678 --> 33:54.662
the fact that you have
no prior convictions

33:54.674 --> 33:56.686
and order a Good Behaviour Bond.

33:56.702 --> 33:59.734
However, as an officer of the court,
you should have known better.

34:00.650 --> 34:02.710
Your conduct must be
of a higher standard.

34:02.726 --> 34:06.722
Therefore, I'm sentencing you
to a community based order

34:06.734 --> 34:09.641
for a period of six months,

34:09.658 --> 34:11.658
during which you shall be
required

34:11.674 --> 34:14.654
to perform 40 hours
of community work

34:14.666 --> 34:16.641
and attend upon a psychologist

34:16.654 --> 34:17.714
for no less than six months,

34:17.730 --> 34:19.681
that being the duration
of the order.

34:20.726 --> 34:23.726
If I was going to go down, I
should have taken Clarke with me,

34:24.641 --> 34:26.658
instead of grovelling like that
in front of him.

34:26.674 --> 34:28.730
That's the most sickening thing
I've ever done.

34:29.646 --> 34:31.658
My mouth was so dry
I couldn't even look at him.

34:31.674 --> 34:33.678
I bet he was smiling.
He wasn't smiling.

34:33.694 --> 34:35.686
The only thing that made me
keep my mouth shut

34:35.702 --> 34:37.694
was knowing he was going
to get convicted.

34:37.710 --> 34:39.714
We can't use
the Ruby Moreno photo.

34:39.726 --> 34:41.730
What? Why?

34:42.417 --> 34:44.697
Moreno gave us information
on the whole Blakely porn ring.

34:44.714 --> 34:47.666
Ruby's photo was the trade-off.
Clarke gets away with it?

34:47.681 --> 34:50.646
For now. He's on the cops' radar,
though. He'll fuck up again.

34:50.661 --> 34:52.503
And you guys didn't tell me
because you thought

34:52.641 --> 34:53.674
I needed protecting?

34:54.702 --> 34:57.666
Now I feel just a little bit
patronised.

34:57.682 --> 35:00.658
I'm sorry. It's just
that you were so nervous.

35:00.674 --> 35:02.154
Oh, with good reason,
as it turns out.

35:02.413 --> 35:04.694
You should let the Law Society
know about your conviction,

35:04.710 --> 35:06.662
rather than them finding out
through the system.

35:06.674 --> 35:07.670
Take the initiative.

35:07.686 --> 35:09.766
Oh, you can actually say
something useful. And legal.

35:14.658 --> 35:17.678
I wish I'd never laid eyes
on Timothy Clarke.

35:17.694 --> 35:20.642
How did you end up in the same
random car park as Clarke?

35:22.702 --> 35:25.682
He suggested you do
something dodgy, didn't he?

35:25.698 --> 35:29.646
Yes, I did. Found his address and
told her he was a very bad man.

35:29.662 --> 35:31.706
The dodginess was my instigation.
Uh, uh, don't protect him.

35:31.718 --> 35:32.706
I'm not.

35:37.674 --> 35:41.694
So, got any more juicy stories
for the tabloids?

35:41.710 --> 35:44.698
Look, Erin,
I'm really sorry about that.

35:44.714 --> 35:48.694
I don't want an apology.
You actually did me a favour.

35:48.710 --> 35:50.698
Proved to me you're not
my type at all.

35:50.710 --> 35:52.666
I could have lost my job.

35:59.694 --> 36:01.642
How'd you go?

36:02.650 --> 36:05.670
I got convicted and he walks.

36:05.682 --> 36:07.686
So much for justice.

36:11.698 --> 36:14.714
We could use someone like you
in the force.

36:14.726 --> 36:17.650
I'm not big on uniforms.

36:17.666 --> 36:19.682
Come straight in
at detective level.

36:19.698 --> 36:22.650
You know, you've got plenty
of experience in criminal law.

36:22.662 --> 36:24.023
That's got to count for something.

36:24.642 --> 36:25.694
Thanks.

36:25.706 --> 36:28.642
But I want to be a lawyer.

36:28.658 --> 36:32.662
I'm good at it, when I'm not
assaulting perpetrators.

36:32.674 --> 36:33.714
Yes. Yes, you are.

36:33.730 --> 36:36.662
And you know what else?
What?

36:36.678 --> 36:39.730
I'm proud that your first instinct
was to save someone in trouble.

36:40.646 --> 36:43.682
And it's what makes you
such a good lawyer.

37:23.666 --> 37:25.682
I believe
there's some good news.

37:25.694 --> 37:27.662
Yes, there is.

37:32.670 --> 37:34.674
Can I have a look?

37:37.646 --> 37:41.654
Drew seemed so, I don't know,
weak or something.

37:41.666 --> 37:42.714
But to kill a judge?

37:42.730 --> 37:45.730
Well, he hasn't admitted to
killing Renmark, not yet anyway.

37:46.642 --> 37:47.682
There's his father too.

37:47.694 --> 37:49.674
Blakely was a big, strong man.

37:49.690 --> 37:51.670
With enough motive,
you can do anything.

37:58.650 --> 38:00.658
Hang on a second.

38:03.658 --> 38:05.638
See this?

38:05.654 --> 38:08.650
You stab me in the eye with this
pen and you could kill me, Janet.

38:09.650 --> 38:11.650
Can you see the initials
on that pen?

38:11.662 --> 38:15.722
Mm. G and R, I think.

38:16.558 --> 38:18.678
Well, that'd be right,
wouldn't it? Granville Renmark?

38:18.694 --> 38:20.694
I just need to make a phone call.
Do you mind?

38:20.706 --> 38:21.710
Sure.

38:26.646 --> 38:29.674
Andy?
Hey, Janet.

38:29.686 --> 38:31.662
Hey, come over for a drink.

38:31.674 --> 38:32.718
Look, I was just wondering,

38:32.734 --> 38:34.690
that pen that was found
with Renmark's body.

38:34.702 --> 38:36.670
Was that ever DNA tested?

38:36.686 --> 38:39.690
What's the interest
in the fountain pen?

38:40.710 --> 38:42.706
Sounds like you're having a party.

38:42.722 --> 38:45.698
We cracked the code, didn't we?
Fat bastard, we got him.

38:45.710 --> 38:47.690
Yeah, Jack's shouting the drinks.

38:47.706 --> 38:51.706
Look, I might leave you to it.
Lina?

38:52.706 --> 38:54.666
Can I borrow your phone?
Yeah.

38:54.682 --> 38:56.718
Thanks.
Are you OK?

39:08.682 --> 39:10.650
You're joking, right?

39:10.666 --> 39:12.714
That pen belongs to Jack Rizzoli.
I've seen it.

39:12.730 --> 39:14.702
He talked about it
being a murder weapon.

39:14.718 --> 39:18.686
Do you remember that?
GR. Giacomo Rizzoli.

39:18.702 --> 39:20.710
And it puts him at the scene
of Renmark's death.

39:20.726 --> 39:22.714
Why would he not say
he was there with Renmark

39:22.726 --> 39:24.686
unless he's hiding something?

39:24.698 --> 39:25.734
Shit.

39:26.650 --> 39:29.654
So Rizzoli told Owen that
I was reporting on him for silk.

39:29.670 --> 39:31.670
Renmark was on the silk selection
committee.

39:31.686 --> 39:33.366
He led us in completely
the wrong direction

39:33.642 --> 39:34.678
for the Moreno defence.

39:34.694 --> 39:37.658
When we first dragged him in,
he was on about being an artist.

39:37.674 --> 39:39.698
Then his lawyer turned up,
told him to put a sock in it.

39:39.714 --> 39:42.666
If you want my opinion, that's
the line they'll run with.

39:42.682 --> 39:44.666
He pushed us to prosecute
Dianne Vasilich,

39:44.678 --> 39:45.702
before Blakely's body was found.

39:45.718 --> 39:48.666
He took me off the task force
in the middle of everything.

39:48.682 --> 39:50.883
I'm running the investigation
into the biggest shitstorm

39:51.369 --> 39:52.690
this department has seen
in years!

39:52.706 --> 39:55.694
I know. I tried to suggest somebody
else but they wouldn't budge.

39:55.710 --> 39:58.690
Don't worry, the task force
continues, just without you.

39:58.702 --> 40:00.678
And he gave Drew his alibi.

40:00.694 --> 40:03.698
Drew only confessed
about Renmark and the bomb

40:03.710 --> 40:04.870
after Jack had been with him.

40:06.654 --> 40:09.638
Maybe Renmark wasn't
behind the bomb.

40:09.650 --> 40:10.690
It was Jack.

40:10.706 --> 40:12.706
He tried to kill me
and my family...

40:14.646 --> 40:16.662
..when he thought I got too close
to the truth.

40:18.650 --> 40:20.690
Does he know that you were
coming here, meeting me?

40:20.706 --> 40:22.682
No, it's OK.
I thought I was meeting Lina.

40:22.698 --> 40:24.642
'Cause he could have people
anywhere.

40:24.654 --> 40:25.718
OK, you take the taxi.

40:25.734 --> 40:27.686
You head straight
to the safe house.

40:27.698 --> 40:29.650
You do not call anyone. No-one.

40:29.666 --> 40:31.638
I told Ash to come home.
I will call her.

40:31.654 --> 40:33.694
Don't tell her anything.
I won't worry her, I promise.

40:33.710 --> 40:35.682
We'll get some security guys
for you, OK?

40:35.698 --> 40:37.694
You stay there
until you hear from me.

41:20.666 --> 41:22.678
Andy, it's me.

41:22.694 --> 41:26.638
There are no security guards
here yet. What's happening?

41:27.666 --> 41:28.714
Can you call me?

41:37.678 --> 41:38.722
OK, you listen to me.

41:38.893 --> 41:40.694
I don't give a fuck
how short-staffed you are.

41:40.710 --> 41:42.682
I want security back
on that safe house now.

41:42.694 --> 41:43.734
Call me when it's done.

41:44.650 --> 41:46.682
I also need someone to run
a mobile number for me.

41:46.694 --> 41:49.638
0491 570 159.

41:49.654 --> 41:53.654
I want to know where that phone
was on Thursday the 4th.

41:56.646 --> 42:00.698
Come on, Andy. Come on.

42:00.710 --> 42:03.638
Oh, thank God.

42:03.650 --> 42:05.678
You know, I was just about...

42:07.678 --> 42:11.686
Jack.
Janet.

42:11.702 --> 42:14.698
I've cancelled the security guys.
You don't need them.

42:14.714 --> 42:16.682
Thought I'd give you
the VIP treatment.

42:16.694 --> 42:18.662
Drive you home myself.

42:18.678 --> 42:21.670
Ah, my car's still at
the police headquarters...

42:21.682 --> 42:23.658
I got it out. It's right here.

42:23.674 --> 42:26.654
Thought you'd like things to be
as normal as possible.

42:27.726 --> 42:30.670
That's very thoughtful of you.

42:32.670 --> 42:33.698
Look, it's late

42:33.714 --> 42:35.674
and I'm happy to drive myself home
in the morning...

42:35.690 --> 42:37.658
It's the least I can do.
I haven't packed.

42:37.674 --> 42:40.642
Everything's really unorganised.
Sort it out tomorrow.

42:42.682 --> 42:45.662
What you need now is a night
underneath your own roof. Come on.

43:46.670 --> 43:48.662
Leave it.

43:54.674 --> 43:56.662
I said fucking leave it!

44:22.674 --> 44:24.686
Don't be so fucking stupid!

45:06.658 --> 45:07.686
Get out.

45:07.702 --> 45:10.638
No-one's going to believe
I killed myself.

45:10.654 --> 45:13.678
I don't want to hurt you.
I just want to talk to you.

45:13.694 --> 45:17.674
Talk? Like you talked
to Renmark, and Blakely?

45:17.686 --> 45:20.662
I didn't kill Blakely.

45:20.678 --> 45:25.678
Drew did. He hated him.
Now get out of the car.

45:36.650 --> 45:37.710
Walk.

45:39.694 --> 45:41.642
Walk!

46:00.658 --> 46:03.666
Andy knows you ran the ring
with Steven.

46:03.678 --> 46:05.646
Steven?

46:06.666 --> 46:10.674
He had nothing to do with it.
It was Drew.

46:10.690 --> 46:13.642
I was watching it for months
before I realised it was him.

46:14.706 --> 46:17.650
You dropped your pen
when you killed Renmark.

46:22.650 --> 46:27.698
This one?
From the evidence room? Huh?

46:29.662 --> 46:30.862
Now you ready to listen to me?

46:33.654 --> 46:38.710
I wanted good people to be safe.
Just like you do.

46:40.698 --> 46:42.698
That's all I want.

46:42.714 --> 46:46.670
All those sickos,
they're not gonna stop.

46:46.686 --> 46:48.642
If they don't get
the stuff from Drew,

46:48.658 --> 46:51.670
they'll just get it off the net
or some other place.

46:51.686 --> 46:56.690
Right now, at this moment,
they'll do whatever I say.

46:56.706 --> 47:01.670
I have this power
over powerful people.

47:01.682 --> 47:02.722
The system works.

47:03.638 --> 47:05.662
This state hasn't been
this safe for years.

47:05.678 --> 47:09.666
All I need is you to keep quiet.

47:09.678 --> 47:11.642
Keep quiet?

47:14.722 --> 47:17.646
You tried to kill my children.

47:18.385 --> 47:19.706
They were never going
to get hurt.

47:19.718 --> 47:21.658
It was a fuckin' bomb.

47:21.674 --> 47:23.718
It was controlled!
Now listen to me.

47:23.734 --> 47:27.642
All the kids in those photos,
from Eastern Europe,

47:27.654 --> 47:29.694
they are impossible to identify.

47:29.706 --> 47:30.694
Impossible.

47:30.710 --> 47:33.686
I can't do anything, nothing
at all, to help those people.

47:33.702 --> 47:35.714
It's not just about
those children.

47:35.726 --> 47:38.638
It's about Ruby Moreno.

47:38.654 --> 47:40.666
It's every kid that Alex Moreno
took a photo of,

47:40.682 --> 47:42.658
it's every kid
in the Blakely beach house.

47:42.670 --> 47:43.694
They are all under your care.

47:43.710 --> 47:46.690
Those images give me
a way of controlling things,

47:46.702 --> 47:48.638
a way we'd lost.

47:48.650 --> 47:50.714
You are sacrificing children.

47:52.662 --> 47:53.694
I'll resign.

47:53.710 --> 47:58.694
OK? I'll resign. I'll walk away.
Yeah, I'll just walk away.

47:58.710 --> 48:01.710
You can prosecute all the guys
in that ring, all of 'em.

48:01.726 --> 48:03.706
And let me tell you,
there's a lot of them.

48:03.722 --> 48:05.702
But it'll shut down
without me and Drew.

48:05.714 --> 48:07.686
It will. It'll shut down.

48:10.698 --> 48:14.642
You just don't get it, do you?
You don't get it!

48:14.654 --> 48:15.730
If I go to prison,

48:16.646 --> 48:18.682
every case that I've worked on
in the last decade,

48:18.698 --> 48:20.178
all of them,
every single one of them,

48:20.642 --> 48:21.670
they will be overturned.

48:21.682 --> 48:22.718
They will be appealed.

48:22.734 --> 48:24.722
And that's a lot of offenders
back out there.

48:25.326 --> 48:27.686
You want to be part of putting
that scum back on the street?

48:27.702 --> 48:30.686
Listen, I'm not taking responsibility
for anything you've done.

48:30.702 --> 48:36.722
Janet, I just... need you
to get on board.

48:36.734 --> 48:38.670
Or what?

48:39.702 --> 48:41.654
Are you going to get rid of me?

48:43.650 --> 48:48.642
There's Novak, Moreno, Tony,
they all know things.

48:48.658 --> 48:50.706
Andy'll know I'm missing.
He'll have alerted people.

48:54.658 --> 48:59.682
Please. Please, Janet.

49:01.658 --> 49:02.858
You can help me convince them.

49:03.638 --> 49:04.718
I won't help you.

49:07.730 --> 49:11.714
If you want to keep me quiet,
you're gonna have to kill me.

49:18.666 --> 49:20.670
Please.

51:14.658 --> 51:17.690
So the cops have charged
everyone involved.

51:17.706 --> 51:22.646
You wanted all this sorted out.
Neat little ribbon.

51:22.662 --> 51:23.718
A second high-ranking
police officer dead

51:23.734 --> 51:25.702
was not exactly
what I had in mind.

51:25.718 --> 51:27.670
Yes, well a lot of things
have happened

51:27.686 --> 51:29.650
which are not exactly
what we had in mind.

51:29.666 --> 51:32.670
Tragic.
Yes, tragic.

51:32.686 --> 51:36.662
Jack was a fine man.
Not exactly the words I'd choose.

51:36.674 --> 51:38.678
A great loss for the public.

51:38.694 --> 51:40.694
Are you actually going
to do this?

51:40.710 --> 51:42.694
What'd be the point of doing
anything else?

51:42.710 --> 51:44.698
It'd destroy the public faith
in the force.

51:44.714 --> 51:47.706
Well, we wouldn't want
to destroy anyone's faith.

51:47.722 --> 51:50.722
I appreciate your support,
you and your department,

51:50.734 --> 51:52.670
at this difficult time.

51:52.686 --> 51:54.086
I know you worked closely
with Jack.

51:54.321 --> 51:55.682
It must be devastating
for you all.

51:55.694 --> 51:57.730
Yes, quite devastating.

51:58.642 --> 52:00.674
But you're to be congratulated.

52:00.690 --> 52:02.678
I believe that
without the tireless work

52:02.690 --> 52:04.678
of you and your departments,

52:04.694 --> 52:07.658
some of these perpetrators
might not have been apprehended.

52:07.674 --> 52:11.654
Well, we do what we can.
You're way too modest.

52:11.670 --> 52:14.646
Under your leadership,
the department is flourishing.

52:14.662 --> 52:16.662
Which brings me to
the purpose of this meeting.

52:16.674 --> 52:17.710
Ah, the purpose.

52:17.726 --> 52:21.710
In light of the achievements
of you and your staff,

52:21.726 --> 52:24.646
I'd like to increase
your funding.

52:24.662 --> 52:26.698
I'm thinking
an extra 10 million a year.

52:26.714 --> 52:29.678
I'm sure you'd be able
to put that to good use.

52:29.694 --> 52:32.642
In light of our achievements
with Blakely,

52:32.654 --> 52:34.702
and other related matters.

52:34.718 --> 52:38.662
Exactly.
I see.

52:38.678 --> 52:42.670
Well, if you're that pleased
with our achievements,

52:42.686 --> 52:45.658
perhaps you could stretch it
to an extra 20 million.

52:46.658 --> 52:50.642
I'm sure with a little shuffling
we could manage 20 million.

52:50.658 --> 52:52.734
We can find a way
to arrange that.

52:53.646 --> 52:55.702
Good. Then we're agreed.

52:55.714 --> 52:58.658
It appears we are.

53:02.730 --> 53:06.734
Giacomo, Jack Rizzoli,

53:07.650 --> 53:09.666
served his community
with distinction

53:09.678 --> 53:11.694
for more than 30 years.

53:11.710 --> 53:14.694
He joined the police officer
straight from school,

53:14.706 --> 53:17.650
intent on a life of public service.

53:18.662 --> 53:20.650
There was no doubt
in anyone's mind

53:20.666 --> 53:23.642
that he would move quickly
through the ranks.

53:23.654 --> 53:25.710
His intelligence, his courage,

53:25.726 --> 53:28.678
his support of his
fellow officers,

53:28.690 --> 53:30.666
his exemplary character,

53:30.682 --> 53:32.726
all these attributes
were apparent in Jack

53:33.642 --> 53:35.686
from very early in his career.

53:35.702 --> 53:39.638
He was a mentor
and friend to many.

53:39.654 --> 53:42.638
It would not be too much to say
that he was, indeed,

53:42.654 --> 53:45.690
an inspiration to all
who worked with him.

53:45.706 --> 53:48.706
What a bloody circus.
Should have brought a bucket.

53:48.722 --> 53:52.722
Although we mourn his loss today
as colleague and friend,

53:53.638 --> 53:55.638
we can take comfort in the fact

53:55.654 --> 53:57.654
that he leaves behind
a fine legacy,

53:57.670 --> 54:00.726
and a police force inspired
by his example.

54:05.690 --> 54:08.650
Thinking of expanding
the department.

54:08.666 --> 54:11.654
A dozen extra solicitors.
What do you think?

54:11.670 --> 54:16.702
Half a dozen crowns?
Think about it.

54:17.726 --> 54:22.698
Hymn number 345,
We Shall Sleep, But Not Forever.

54:22.714 --> 54:25.722
A right royal piss-up is required
after this charade.

54:26.638 --> 54:29.714
Not with this mob of arselickers.
You and me and Andy Campbell.

54:29.730 --> 54:32.698
Drink to forget.
It's on the department.

54:32.710 --> 54:35.638
We've come into a bit of money.

54:56.670 --> 54:59.722
The government throws a good bash
when they're rewriting history.

55:00.638 --> 55:02.646
Oh, it's happened before,
it'll happen again.

55:02.662 --> 55:05.690
At least this time all the bad guys
are dead or in jail,

55:05.702 --> 55:07.638
which serves the rest of us.

55:07.654 --> 55:10.666
For the greater good.

55:10.678 --> 55:12.662
There's another conspiracy.

55:12.678 --> 55:16.674
She'll go to the grave believing
she had the perfect son.

55:16.686 --> 55:18.646
Pub?

55:18.658 --> 55:20.690
Another time. I've got a date.

55:26.678 --> 55:28.722
Have fun at the pub.

55:30.730 --> 55:32.698
Shall we?

55:32.714 --> 55:35.650
They're not expecting us
back at work, are they?

55:35.666 --> 55:37.710
Probably.
Stop worrying about Tracey.

55:37.726 --> 55:40.698
We're drinking because
we earned it. And it's on Andy.

55:40.714 --> 55:42.722
Yeah!
Oh, I don't think so.

55:42.734 --> 55:44.678
Thanks, Andy.

